1
00:00:02,765 --> 00:00:05,802
In 2019, PhD candidate Steve Jacobs

2
00:00:05,802 --> 00:00:09,172
surveyed thousands of
biology professors and found

3
00:00:09,172 --> 00:00:13,843
that 96% of them
believed life begins at conception.

4
00:00:13,843 --> 00:00:19,582
Out of the 5,577 biologists surveyed, 85%

5
00:00:19,582 --> 00:00:24,420
identified as
pro-choice and 63% as non-religious.

6
00:00:24,420 --> 00:00:28,024
Now Jacobs wasn't trying
to support the pro-life position.

7
00:00:28,024 --> 00:00:30,059
Instead, he found
himself trying to explain

8
00:00:30,059 --> 00:00:32,895
how so many
biologists could be pro-choice

9
00:00:32,895 --> 00:00:35,932
while acknowledging
life begins at conception.

10
00:00:35,932 --> 00:00:38,401
He wrote,
"Philosophers such as Peter Singer

11
00:00:38,401 --> 00:00:41,504
and Judith Jarvis
Thompson have outlined abortion

12
00:00:41,504 --> 00:00:44,374
defenses that
recognize a fetus's humanity

13
00:00:44,374 --> 00:00:47,510
while also rejecting
the argument that fetuses

14
00:00:47,510 --> 00:00:48,678
have rights."

15
00:00:48,678 --> 00:00:51,614
First, let's explore why murder is wrong.

16
00:00:51,614 --> 00:00:53,650
If your worldview says all living things

17
00:00:53,650 --> 00:00:57,053
evolved by random
processes over billions of years,

18
00:00:57,053 --> 00:01:01,991
then it's logical to conclude humans
are no more valuable than chimpanzees, trees,

19
00:01:01,991 --> 00:01:03,192
or insects.

20
00:01:03,192 --> 00:01:05,228
For the humanist, humans are the highest

21
00:01:05,228 --> 00:01:07,463
form of life and
deserve the greatest amount of

22
00:01:07,463 --> 00:01:08,398
respect.

23
00:01:08,398 --> 00:01:10,800
But God is higher than all creation, and

24
00:01:10,800 --> 00:01:13,302
only He gets to
decide what is morally right or

25
00:01:13,302 --> 00:01:13,870
wrong.

26
00:01:13,870 --> 00:01:20,143
In Genesis 9.6, God says, "Whoever
sheds the blood of man by man shall his blood be

27
00:01:20,143 --> 00:01:23,746
shed, for God made man in his own image."

28
00:01:23,746 --> 00:01:25,448
Humans are created distinct from other

29
00:01:25,448 --> 00:01:28,684
creatures, and killing a
human is particularly serious

30
00:01:28,684 --> 00:01:31,988
because it involves
destroying an image-bearer.

31
00:01:31,988 --> 00:01:34,824
But then there's the
fuzzy concept of personhood.

32
00:01:34,824 --> 00:01:36,025
Wait, humans are fuzzy?

33
00:01:36,025 --> 00:01:37,126
No, persons.

34
00:01:37,126 --> 00:01:40,029
But wait, aren't
humans and persons the same thing?

35
00:01:40,029 --> 00:01:42,565
Apparently, not everyone thinks so.

36
00:01:42,565 --> 00:01:44,767
Peter Singer, professor of bioethics at

37
00:01:44,767 --> 00:01:48,037
Princeton University,
wrote, "Human babies are not

38
00:01:48,037 --> 00:01:52,642
born self-aware or capable of
grasping that they exist over time.

39
00:01:52,642 --> 00:01:53,976
They are not persons.

40
00:01:53,976 --> 00:01:56,379
But animals are self-aware, and therefore

41
00:01:56,379 --> 00:01:59,248
the life of a
newborn is of less value than

42
00:01:59,248 --> 00:02:02,418
the life of a pig,
a dog, or a chimpanzee."

43
00:02:02,418 --> 00:02:03,753
That's ridiculous.

44
00:02:03,753 --> 00:02:08,624
The idea is that biology determines
humanity, but personhood determines worth.

45
00:02:08,624 --> 00:02:10,860
However, it's always been dangerous to

46
00:02:10,860 --> 00:02:13,763
question the
personhood of certain human beings.

47
00:02:13,763 --> 00:02:17,600
Such thinking has led to
things like slavery and the Holocaust.

48
00:02:17,600 --> 00:02:19,702
In fact, in
Canada, at one time women were

49
00:02:19,702 --> 00:02:22,572
denied the vote
because they were not considered

50
00:02:22,572 --> 00:02:23,940
persons either.

51
00:02:23,940 --> 00:02:25,408
Yet, ironically, some of the folks

52
00:02:25,408 --> 00:02:28,911
currently denying
personhood to pre-born babies are

53
00:02:28,911 --> 00:02:29,912
women.

54
00:02:29,912 --> 00:02:30,746
Ouch.

55
00:02:30,746 --> 00:02:34,083
That sounds harsh, but
consider a common scenario.

56
00:02:34,083 --> 00:02:36,285
A woman finds out she's pregnant.

57
00:02:36,285 --> 00:02:38,187
Pro-abortionists would say she alone can

58
00:02:38,187 --> 00:02:41,023
choose to abort or
not because it's her body.

59
00:02:41,023 --> 00:02:43,292
If she decides to keep the baby, studies

60
00:02:43,292 --> 00:02:46,062
indicate she'll
probably make healthy choices during

61
00:02:46,062 --> 00:02:49,198
pregnancy, like abstaining from alcohol.

62
00:02:49,198 --> 00:02:50,133
Great.

63
00:02:50,133 --> 00:02:52,101
But is it for her own health, or is she

64
00:02:52,101 --> 00:02:55,271
taking her pre-born
child into consideration?

65
00:02:55,271 --> 00:02:59,776
Did anyone consider the child when
she was deciding whether or not to abort?

66
00:02:59,776 --> 00:03:01,744
If not, what changed?

67
00:03:01,744 --> 00:03:06,149
Did the baby become a person
because he or she is wanted by the mother?

